<section id="submission" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8 text-primary-800 animate-on-scroll">
        Paper Submission
      </h2>
      
      <div class="mb-12 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 border border-gray-200 animate-on-scroll">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-primary-700">Submission Guidelines</h3>
        
        <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
          <p>
            We invite researchers to submit original, unpublished work related to the workshop themes. All submissions will undergo a rigorous peer-review process by our program committee.
          </p>
          
          <h4 class="font-medium text-primary-700 mt-6">Paper Categories:</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li><span class="font-medium">Full Papers:</span> Up to 8 pages, presenting substantial research contributions.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Short Papers:</span> Up to 4 pages, suitable for work-in-progress or preliminary results.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Position Papers:</span> Up to 2 pages, outlining visionary or controversial ideas to stimulate discussion.</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h4 class="font-medium text-primary-700 mt-6">Formatting Requirements:</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>All submissions must follow the IEEE conference template format.</li>
            <li>Papers must be submitted in PDF format.</li>
            <li>References do not count toward the page limit.</li>
            <li>Submissions should be anonymized for double-blind review.</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h4 class="font-medium text-primary-700 mt-6">Submission System:</h4>
          <p>
            Papers should be submitted through the workshop's submission system. Please create an account on the submission portal to upload your paper.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mt-8 text-center">
          <a href="#" class="bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2 px-6 rounded-md transition-colors duration-300 inline-flex items-center shadow-md">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 mr-2" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M3 17a1 1 0 011-1h12a1 1 0 110 2H4a1 1 0 01-1-1zM6.293 6.707a1 1 0 010-1.414l3-3a1 1 0 011.414 0l3 3a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L11 5.414V13a1 1 0 11-2 0V5.414L7.707 6.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            Submit Your Paper
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 animate-on-scroll">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm p-6 border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-primary-700">Review Process</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Each submission will be reviewed by at least three members of the program committee. The review process will evaluate originality, significance, technical soundness, clarity, and relevance to the workshop themes.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm p-6 border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-primary-700">Publication</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Accepted papers will be published in the workshop proceedings and indexed in major digital libraries. Selected high-quality papers may be invited for extension and publication in a special issue of a reputable journal.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>